  "body": "Current behaviour: passed-in style property\n\n```\n{\n  border:'1px solid #ccc'\n}\n```\n\nwould be translated to\n\n```\n{\n  border-top-color: #ccc,\n  border-top-width: 1px,\n  border-top-style: solid,\n  ...the other border-xxx-xxx\n}\n```\n\nI want the shorthand style property remained unexpanded as [Outlook 2007+ dose not support style properties like border-width, border-color etc.](https://www.campaignmonitor.com/css/) \n\nAlso I found this expanding operation by React is done [here](react/src/renderers/dom/shared/CSSProperty.js) but it's not configurable.\nAny ideas? Thanks in advanced!\n",
